	<div style="padding: 4px;"><span class="postbody">All I have to ask is WHY? why? why?
<br />

<br />
First let me preface my statements with this: I love EQ2 much more then EQ1. I played EQ1 from release. I had a 65 Cleric with some AA's and his Epic in EQ1, before I retired from EQ1. Needless to say, I'm not new to the MMoRPG world..particularly EQ.
<br />

<br />
/rant on
<br />

<br />
Last night I encountered my first EQ2 Battle Cleric. I'm an 18.5 Cleric. I grouped with a bunch of folks to do the Firemyst Gulley encounter. We had Myself, Another cleric who shall not be named, A good tank and 2 solid dps. The named conned ^^orange to me..blue to the tank and dps'rs. Should've been a good fight in which we ultimately should've been victorious. We cleared the zone of all Scathe type skellies, seers and what not, and got down to the Named and 2 of his henchmen (the Goal). Again a difficult fight..but one that was winnable.
<br />

<br />
Needless to say..we wiped. We got the named down to 30%. I used Soothing Sermon and BoV ALOT. I had to hehe. Unfortunately there were a number of instances where they both got dispelled in AE type spells. Everything was going well until I started to run low on power..mind you we had another cleric in the group who was still at about 75% power. The Tank dropped (usually suggests that the group is about to wipe) followed by the DPS.. still no heals from the other cleric. We wiped and found ourselves sitting outside of FMG waiting to right click to recover our shards.
<br />

<br />
The tank asked the other cleric why they were meleeing and casting the occasional nuke.. His response:
<br />

<br />
"Dude, I'm a Battle Cleric..not a @#$%@ healer. I thought thats why we had the second cleric."
<br />

<br />
It's so funny and abysmal at the same time, you can't help but shake your head.
<br />

<br />
Needless to say the group disbanded..unfortunately 2 disbanded before they recovered their shards so those of us remaining had to eat their full debt along with our own.
<br />

<br />
Moral of the story: If you run into someone who is a "Battle Cleric"..be sure to disband immediately. No good can come of it.
<br />

<br />
Also..if you're grouped with a cleric who doesn't use macros to communicate or cast heals and other Cleric type thingies..disband as well. Macros are easy to create..the info has been available on how to create them for a couple months..please please please..if you are a cleric, Make some Hotkeys to cast and communicate. They are a necessity to progression and good grouping and also instill a sense of confidence in the group to see in chat that a heal is on the way. Theres nothing more infuriating then watching Tanks and DPS'rs scream "HEAL", and you are a secondary healer. I have been balled out twice for healing as a secondary cleric..by a cleric who doesn't use macros. I can't be a mind reader and watching their power bar without knowing what they are casting is a waste of time. My experience in FMG taught me to never trust that another Cleric is going to heal..especially when they don't have any communication skills.
<br />

<br />
/rant off</span></div>
	</td>
</tr>
