	<div style="padding: 4px;"><span class="postbody">There's nothing wrong with battle clerics. There's something wrong with idiots who don't pay attention. It's kinda like having a bus crash and the driver goes "Well, there were all these other people who can drive so I figured they'd pick up the slack".
<br />

<br />
This guy had heals and yet he didn't use them. That's not a battle cleric, that's a wannabe tank or wizard. Simply put, he assumed you were all the healing necessary. Assuptions can be very dangerous...
<br />

<br />
The only thing you can do is to make sure you make sure everyone knows what their jobs are and that they get done.</span></div>
	</td>
