	<div style="padding: 4px;"><span class="postbody"><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2" border="0" align="center" class="quote"><tr>	<td class="quote">Moral of the story: If you run into someone who is a "Battle Cleric"..be sure to disband immediately. No good can come of it. </td>	</tr></table>
<br />

<br />
Sounds like he should have been a pally.  While we can take some hits due to the heavy plate, we are not dps.
<br />

<br />
<table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2" border="0" align="center" class="quote"><tr>	<td class="quote">Also..if you're grouped with a cleric who doesn't use macros to communicate or cast heals and other Cleric type thingies..disband as well.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table>
<br />

<br />
I disagree.  I have not yet made a single macro in EQ2 and I do quite fine.  I group quite often with other healers, tho usually its a different class, so we just decide beforehand to use combos of regen/bov and I do the instahealing or ward/bov etc.
<br />

<br />
Besides which - I don't expect all tanks to sit there and call out a macro everytime they taunt or hit the mob.  I expect them to do their job.  If I find the tank is not gaining or holding aggro and I am healing properly (i.e. not on pull), then I question them, if they continue to play like a tard, then I disband, with an explanation why.
<br />

<br />
I just don't agree that whether someone has a macro or not is any indication of whether they are a worthwhile cleric or not.
<br />

<br />
As for trusting another cleric to heal - perhaps you should approach it the way I do - you watch to be sure everyone knows how to play their class well enough i.e. the group is working together well.  If not, you identify why and talk about it.
<br />
[/quote]</span></div>
	</td>
</tr>
