Well..I'll agree to disagree with you on this one. Communication is KEY. I can't tell you how many times so far that multiple heals (wasting power..aka inefficient grouping and added downtime) have been thrown or HO's have been interrupted due to lack of macros (AKA Communication Tools), while grouping because a backup healer or a MH don't use macros to communicate a cast or someone doesn't call out an HO. You may get lucky and group often with folks that you know, but for everyday gaming Pickup groups are the norm..and communication can make a bad group ALOT more bearable.
<br />

<br />
A Healer class (regardless of what particular class) in general is the Anchor of every group. You can't control the group without communication. Dead Air drives me insane.
<br />

<br />
The concept of a "Battle Cleric" in my opinion is still pretty lame. Play a Hybrid if you want to be a damage dealer and heal.
<br />

