	<div style="padding: 4px;"><span class="postbody">Please be patient with me.   I'm a level 12 Cleric in a brand new world.  I played EQ long time ago when it was first on the market but haven't played it for years.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I've never played a cleric but I think it's the profession that is ideal for me.  However, I am having some problems and they result in me dying all too often.  I seem to remember that one of the most important things about a cleric was keeping her alive.  When being hit on, not only does she have to be concerned with yet another life line (hers) but the interruptions of her heals are likely.   
<br />

<br />

<br />
Ok.... yesterday, in a group of a tank (I don't remember now what profession he was but he was our main tank), a scout and me, I was told by the tank to get in there and start swinging with my sword.   
<br />

<br />

<br />
Wouldn't this result in even more attention from the monsters then I was already getting with my heals?   I've been working hard on trying to keep them alive with the milder heals at first so as not to attract the monster's attention.  Is my memory or my manner faulty?
<br />

<br />

<br />
When I started getting hit on, no one even bothered to change to the monster hitting me.  This resulted in my death at least three times with this group..... and none of them died too.  Groups are hard to find so I stayed with them but what should I have said or done?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Ok, next question.   Can you tell me the micros you are talking about?   And maybe tell me or direct me to where I can find out how to install them?   
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Next to last question (probably)..... where is a good place to find out what the spells I am getting really do.    I am confused about what a "spirit guide" is or if one of the revive things can be used on me and there was another one but I can't remember now that I'm out of the game.   And they are labeled with Apprentice I and I've no clue what the Apprentice title means.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
Last question (for now).  What is "dps"?</span></div>
