	<div style="padding: 4px;"><span class="postbody"><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2" border="0" align="center" class="quote"><tr> 	<td class="quote_user">Blaz wrote:</td></tr><tr>	<td class="quote">Please be patient with me.   I'm a level 12 Cleric in a brand new world.  I played EQ long time ago when it was first on the market but haven't played it for years. </td>	</tr></table>
<br />

<br />
Cool... Welcome to the team. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> The healing team. LOL I played EQL/EQ1 for years, but never a cleric. You aren't in a bad boat, I assure you. THe two games are completely different. In fact, I hated clerics during the first one, but love my Templar.
<br />

<br />
I<table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2" border="0" align="center" class="quote"><tr> 	<td class="quote_user">Blaz wrote:</td></tr><tr>	<td class="quote">'ve never played a cleric but I think it's the profession that is ideal for me.  However, I am having some problems and they result in me dying all too often.  I seem to remember that one of the most important things about a cleric was keeping her alive.  When being hit on, not only does she have to be concerned with yet another life line (hers) but the interruptions of her heals are likely.   </td>	</tr></table>
<br />

<br />
True, and the time will come when you have to deal with both at the same time or someone dies. AOE (Area of Effect) heals are perfect for this situation. As for being interupted. Well, it will happen until you get your skills up high enough to cast through it. THe skills will go up on their own by just playing the game. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />
<table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2" border="0" align="center" class="quote"><tr> 	<td class="quote_user">Blaz wrote:</td></tr><tr>	<td class="quote">Ok.... yesterday, in a group of a tank (I don't remember now what profession he was but he was our main tank), a scout and me, I was told by the tank to get in there and start swinging with my sword.  
<br />

<br />
Wouldn't this result in even more attention from the monsters then I was already getting with my heals?   I've been working hard on trying to keep them alive with the milder heals at first so as not to attract the monster's attention.  Is my memory or my manner faulty?</td>	</tr></table>
<br />

<br />
This is a matter of personal perference. I do the whole hammer swinging thing, but some people don't. In EQ2, you can assist someone by targetting them and pressing the attack key. In EQ1 you couldn't do that. Hence, clerics could not do two things at once. Also remember, if you are fighting a mob and you cast a heal, the heal will go to whatever the mob is beating on, another nice feature of EQ2.
<br />

<br />
Your swinging a sword won't add much to the monster's attention level --Agro. But, it will add to the dps(Damage Per Second) being done by the group. Also, using those skills will help you do better damage as your skills improve. But....You shouldn't be getting agro.  The main tank, Paladin, Shadow Knight, Berzerker, Guardian, should be managing the agrivation level of the monster you are fighting, i.e. All the mobs in the zone SHOULD hate the tank more than you. Also, you (if memory serves correctly) have a spell called distract....Use it to give agro back to the tank, they'll appreciate that.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2" border="0" align="center" class="quote"><tr> 	<td class="quote_user">Blaz wrote:</td></tr><tr>	<td class="quote">When I started getting hit on, no one even bothered to change to the monster hitting me.  This resulted in my death at least three times with this group..... and none of them died too.  Groups are hard to find so I stayed with them but what should I have said or done?</td>	</tr></table>
<br />

<br />
Grops for a cleric should not be hard to find. I think the longest I have ever been looking for a group is two minutes...regardless of the zone I was in. But....groups are easy to find, but good groups are hard to find. So, you may have to wade through a few bad ones to develop some reputation to get into the better groups. Hang around in most zones, /ooc that you are looking for a group, and...If you are good...The rest will come. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
<table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2" border="0" align="center" class="quote"><tr> 	<td class="quote_user">Blaz wrote:</td></tr><tr>	<td class="quote">Ok, next question.   Can you tell me the micros you are talking about?   And maybe tell me or direct me to where I can find out how to install them?   </td>	</tr></table>
<br />

<br />
Click on the EQII button.
<br />
Click on the socials button
<br />
Click on the macros button
<br />
Edit one and put whatever you like in there. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />
<table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2" border="0" align="center" class="quote"><tr> 	<td class="quote_user">Blaz wrote:</td></tr><tr>	<td class="quote">Next to last question (probably)..... where is a good place to find out what the spells I am getting really do.    I am confused about what a "spirit guide" is or if one of the revive things can be used on me and there was another one but I can't remember now that I'm out of the game.   And they are labeled with Apprentice I and I've no clue what the Apprentice title means.  </td>	</tr></table>
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://eq2.gamergod.com/spells.cfm" target="_blank">http://eq2.gamergod.com/spells.cfm</a>
<br />

<br />
<table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2" border="0" align="center" class="quote"><tr> 	<td class="quote_user">Blaz wrote:</td></tr><tr>	<td class="quote">Last question (for now).  What is "dps"?</td>	</tr></table>
<br />

<br />
DPS - Damage per Second.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Hope most/ all/ some/ none of that helps. LOL <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />
<br />

